nd","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Scudamore","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Skidmore  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Skidmore","meanings":["English (Staffordshire): of Norman origin, a variant of <b>Scudamore</b>, which most probably arises from a Norman French nickname for a knight who used a particular type of leather shield, from the unrecorded Norman French phrase, <i>escu de more</i> ‘Moor's shield’, a reference to a type of Moorish leather shield called an <i>adarga</i>, which was in widespread use not only in medieval Iberia and north Africa but also in Brittany.","History: The manor of Upton Scudamore in Wiltshire was held by Peter de Skydemore in 1216. The same manor was held by Godfrey Escudamore shortly after 1150. The Scudamore family claim descent from Ralph, recorded in Domesday Book (1086) as holder of <i>Opeton</i> (Upton), whose son was known as Reginald <i>Escudemor</i>."]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph de Scudamore was born in 1050, in Normandy, France, his father, Sir Alexander de Scudamore, was 24 and his mother, Jane Catchman, was 20. He married Miss Erkenwald in 1074, in Kentchurch, Herefordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1120, in Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1050–1120":"1050–1120","1052–1095":"1052–1095","1040–Female":"1040–Surnud","1075–1148":"1075–1148","1026–1052":"1026–1052","1030–1052":"1030–1052","1148":"1148","1026":"1026","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1052":"1052","1074":"1074","1030":"1030","1040":"1040","1095":"1095","1050":"1050","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England":"Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England","Kentchurch, Herefordshire, England":"Kentchurch, Herefordshire, England","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1050–1120":"1050–1120","1052–1095":"1052–1095","1040–Female":"1040–Kuollut","1075–1148":"1075–1148","1026–1052":"1026–1052","1030–1052":"1030–1052","1148":"1148","1026":"1026","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1052":"1052","1074":"1074","1030":"1030","1040":"1040","1095":"1